# Continuous commit and push

Do not wait to be asked to commit or push. Parent agents and Task subagents both follow this.

## When

After a coherent, verified unit of work (owned builds/tests pass), commit immediately, then push to the tracked remote.

## How

- One concern per commit; short human-friendly messages (why, not file lists); HEREDOC `git commit -m`.
- `git push` (or `-u` when first publishing the branch). Never force-push `main`/`master`.
- Keep normal git safety: no config changes, no hook skips, no secrets, amend only under standard amend conditions.

## Subagents

When launching Task/subagents, include explicit instructions to:

1. Commit their completed owned files with granular messages.
2. Push to the current branch on the shared repo (no worktrees/PRs unless separately requested).
3. Stay within assigned file ownership so parallel agents do not clobber each other.

## Parallel work on one branch

Prefer disjoint file ownership. If conflicts appear, finish and commit one agent’s scope before the next touches shared files.
